news.title: Agra: No highrises to be built in 1.5-km radius behind Taj Mahal
news.para: “No construction higher than 25m can come up behind the Taj Mahal so the panoramic view of the monument is visible without an obstruction in the background,” said Dr Rajendra Pensiya, vice chairperson of the Agra Development Authority.

news.title: Government will distribute 13,500 land titles: Kerala CM
news.para: ​The CM, in a post on his Facebook page, said the "pattayam mela" for land allotment will be carried out on Tuesday in 14 district centres and 77 taluk centres in the state.

news.title: About 700 buildings were identified as dangerous in pre-monsoon survey: NDMC
news.para: "During this survey, 699 properties or structures were found in a dangerous condition and 444 structures were identified as needing necessary repairs," a senior NDMC official said.

news.title: Delhi government to provide financial aid to install rainwater harvesting systems
news.para: ​The Delhi Jal Board (DJB) had earlier issued guidelines mandating owners of existing and new properties measuring 100 square metres and above to install RWH structures.

news.title: HFCs' asset under management remains flat in Q1 FY22: Icra Ratings
news.para: "Given this subdued disbursements and portfolio rundown in the absence of any moratorium like in Q1 FY2021, the (AUM) for NBFC-segment shrunk in Q1 FY2022, while the HFC AUM remained flat," the agency said.

news.title: Noida authority asks SC to relook interest rate cap for realtors
news.para: As the bench asked how is it possible to recall the order after one year, against the backdrop of claims that some of the builders might have benefited, counsel submitted that after the top court's June 10 order, everything has been halted. "Not a single paisa has been paid in the last one year," he told the bench.

news.title: Have attached properties worth Rs 4.79 crore of ex-Amrapali director: ED to SC
news.para: The court appointed forensic auditor Pawan Kumar Aggrawal disputed the claims of ED and said that Rs 10.26 crore was outstanding against Prem Mishra and it is recorded in the forensic audit and the 2019 judgement of the court.

news.title: Will adopt best practice to raze Supertech twin towers: CBRI
news.para: The group of experts spent more than two hours at the site and clicked several pictures of the two towers before interacting with residents of the adjacent buildings and members of the residents’ welfare association (RWA).

news.title: Rajasthan: Stamp & registration revenue mop up shows good revival of realty market
news.para: During the April-August this year, the department earned Rs 2224.26 crore compared to Rs 1572.81 crore in the same period last year, posting a growth of over 41%.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body to acquire 260 properties for storm water drains development
news.para: In an effort to fix the city’s drainage system, GHMC’s Strategic Nala Development Programme (SNDP) was rolled out in November 2020 post the floods that created havoc in the city.

news.title: Ludhiana: Construction & demolition waste piles up, recycling project in deep abyss
news.para: The National Green Tribunal (NGT) had directed the MC to start operatiing this C&D waste processing plant in three months or pay a penalty of Rs 2 lakh.

news.title: Mumbai: Builders named in inquiry reports deny any role in trust land fraud
news.para: On January 10, 2014, the then Raigad collector had recommended to the Konkan divisional commissioner to file complaints against those named in the inquiry report, according to documents procured under the RTI by activist Rajeev Mishra.

news.title: NGT disposes plea against Goa Velha building complex
news.para: ​While the activists had alleged that the report of the expert committee formed based on NGT orders were faulty and malafide, the tribunal refused to accept this submission.

news.title: Nagpur improvement trust seeks user change of PU land, ground 'to help a builder'
news.para: ​The PU land is 0.4 hectare (43,056 sq ft), with change in reservation proposed for 0.33 hectare (36,199 sq ft) to residential, and remaining 0.067 hectare (7,212 sq ft) land left as parking.

news.title: Mumbai: Khar-based builder booked for cheating Dubai businessman
news.para: In his complaint, Shadab said the father-son duo approached his father Shabbir in 2014, seeking a financial aid of Rs 50 lakh and agreed to keep their flat at Kamal Vishranti at TPS 3 in Bandra as security with an additional interest of 21% as profit on the borrowed sum.
